# REFERENCE ONLY. The live Caddyfile (~/workspaces/Caddyfile) is GENERATED by
# entrypoint.sh on every pod start — do NOT edit it directly (changes are lost).
# This file documents what gets generated and how to extend it.
#
# Only content you explicitly register is exposed; the rest of ~/workspaces is
# NOT served.
#
#   Publish static HTML/assets:
#       webshare add <name> <dir>     ->  https://<host>/<name>/
#       webshare rm <name>            (unpublish)        webshare list
#     (`webshare` symlinks <dir> into ~/workspaces/.public/. Whatever is INSIDE a
#      published dir becomes public — only publish dirs of public-safe files.)
#
#   Proxy a live app / custom routing:
#       drop a snippet in ~/workspaces/caddy.d/<anything>.caddy, e.g.
#         handle_path /myapp/* { reverse_proxy localhost:8501 }
#
# Two generated shapes, chosen by $CLAUDE_WEB_HOST:
#
#   k8s (host set) — caddy auto-obtains a Let's Encrypt cert and serves HTTPS on
#   :443 (+ :80 redirect). Certs/account persist under ~/workspaces/.caddy.
#
#       {
#           storage file_system /home/claude/workspaces/.caddy
#           email you@example.com          # if CLAUDE_ACME_EMAIL set
#           acme_ca https://...            # if CLAUDE_ACME_CA set (e.g. LE staging)
#       }
#       claude-bajger.dyn.cloud.e-infra.cz {
#           root * /home/claude/workspaces/.public
#           file_server browse
#           import /home/claude/workspaces/caddy.d/*.caddy
#       }
#
#   compose/local (host unset) — plain HTTP on :8080, no TLS:
#
#       :8080 {
#           root * /home/claude/workspaces/.public
#           file_server browse
#           import /home/claude/workspaces/caddy.d/*.caddy
#       }
